OL,3,CChancellor will change fiscal rules
OL,4,Cfor more investment but won't rule out
OL,5,Ccuts
OL,7,FChanges to taxation are possibly the
OL,8,Fmost anticipated part of the
OL,9,FChancellor's Budget on October 30.
OL,11,FIn their manifesto, Labour said they
OL,12,Fwould not "raise taxes on working
OL,13,Fpeople", but comments from the IMF -
OL,14,Fand Keir Starmer's warnings of a
OL,15,F"painful" Budget - have left people
OL,16,Fwondering whether the new government
OL,17,Fwill have to break that pledge.
OL,19,FReeves said on Thursday that Labour
OL,20,F"will stick to those promises in the
OL,21,FBudget".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
