OL,3,CChancellor will change fiscal rules
OL,4,Cfor more investment but won't rule out
OL,5,Ccuts
OL,7,F"Trust in politics is at an all-time
OL,8,Flow, and a lot of that is because
OL,9,Fpromises are made and then they're
OL,10,Fditched. I don't want to be a
OL,11,Fchancellor like that, we don't want to
OL,12,Fbe a government like that and so the
OL,13,Fcommitments that we made in our
OL,14,Fmanifesto, including on tax - the
OL,15,Fordinary working people would not see
OL,16,Fincreases in the National Insurance,
OL,17,Fincome tax or VAT."
OL,19,FThe original commitment has also
OL,20,Fraised questions as to the exact
OL,21,Fdefinition of "working people".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
